<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7934&amp;p=80982#p80982</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7934&amp;p=80982#p80982"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Dreamworld Pogie compiled!]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7934&amp;p=80982#p80982"><![CDATA[
I just looked at the game you are talking about. Notice that there's a big blue area at the bottom of the screen. That's because the game disables rendering 23 or so scanlines earlier, so it more than doubles the VBlank time. This is how this game gets away with updating all those tiles even with a fairly slow loop.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=95">tokumaru</a> — Fri Jul 01, 2011 5:31 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
